<tr id="L72"><td><a href="#L72">72</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  Ma'am. You're food to a starving man. All of you. Hey, that's a nice ship. Simple and clean. Been trying to get her to go again? Well, forget it. It won't work.</td></tr>

<tr id="L73"><td><a href="#L73">73</a></td><td>MCCOY:  He's human, Jim. Everything checks out perfectly.</td></tr>

<tr id="L74"><td><a href="#L74">74</a></td><td>KIRK:  Mister Cochrane. We were forced off our course and taken here by some force we couldn't identify.</td></tr>

<tr id="L75"><td><a href="#L75">75</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Which seems to be on the surface of this body at the moment.</td></tr>

<tr id="L76"><td><a href="#L76">76</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  Well, I wouldn't know anything about that.</td></tr>

<tr id="L77"><td><a href="#L77">77</a></td><td>SPOCK:  You say we'll be unable to get the ship to function again?</td></tr>

<tr id="L78"><td><a href="#L78">78</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  Not a chance. There's some sort of dampening field down here. Power systems don't work. Take my word for it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L79"><td><a href="#L79">79</a></td><td>SPOCK:  You don't mind if we continue to try?</td></tr>

<tr id="L80"><td><a href="#L80">80</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  Go right ahead. You've got plenty of time.</td></tr>

<tr id="L81"><td><a href="#L81">81</a></td><td>KIRK:  What about you, Cochrane? How did you get here?</td></tr>

<tr id="L82"><td><a href="#L82">82</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  Marooned, I told you. Look, we'll have lots of time to learn about each other. I have a small place over that way. All the comforts of home. I can even offer you a hot bath.</td></tr>

<tr id="L83"><td><a href="#L83">83</a></td><td>NANCY:  How perceptive of you to notice I needed one.</td></tr>

<tr id="L84"><td><a href="#L84">84</a></td><td>KIRK:  If you don't mind, Mister Cochrane, I'd like more than just a statement that you were marooned here. It's a long way off the beaten path.</td></tr>

<tr id="L85"><td><a href="#L85">85</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  That's right. That's why I'm so glad to see you. Look, I'll tell you everything you want to know, but not here. Your ship is sure a beauty.</td></tr>

<tr id="L86"><td><a href="#L86">86</a></td><td>KIRK:  Yes, she is. And you've been out of circulation quite a while. The principles may be new to you. Mister Spock, why don't you explain our methods of propulsion to Mister Cochrane?</td></tr>

<tr id="L87"><td><a href="#L87">87</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Spock and Cochrane go to the other side of the shuttlecraft.</td></tr>

<tr id="L88"><td><a href="#L88">88</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Talks a lot, but he doesn't say much.</td></tr>

