<tr id="L112"><td><a href="#L112">112</a></td><td>KIRK:  Yes, I know. It means we're running out of time.</td></tr>

<tr id="L113"><td><a href="#L113">113</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Captain, Doctor.</td></tr>

<tr id="L114"><td><a href="#L114">114</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: From the doorway, the three see a swirly thing which then disappears. Cochrane comes in with a tray of drinks.</td></tr>

<tr id="L115"><td><a href="#L115">115</a></td><td>KIRK:  What was that?</td></tr>

<tr id="L116"><td><a href="#L116">116</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  Well, sometimes the light plays tricks on you. You'd be surprised what I've imagined I've seen around here sometimes.</td></tr>

<tr id="L117"><td><a href="#L117">117</a></td><td>SPOCK:  We imagined nothing, Mister Cochrane. There was an entity out there and I suspect it was the same entity which brought us here. Please explain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L118"><td><a href="#L118">118</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  There's nothing to explain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L119"><td><a href="#L119">119</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: He hands a drink to Nancy.</td></tr>

<tr id="L120"><td><a href="#L120">120</a></td><td>NANCY:  Thank you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L121"><td><a href="#L121">121</a></td><td>KIRK:  You'll find I have a very low tolerance level where the safety of my people are concerned. We find you out here, where no human has any business being. We were virtually hijacked in space and brought here. Now I'm not just requesting an explanation, Mister. I'm demanding one.</td></tr>

<tr id="L122"><td><a href="#L122">122</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  All right. It was the Companion.</td></tr>

<tr id="L123"><td><a href="#L123">123</a></td><td>KIRK:  The what?</td></tr>

<tr id="L124"><td><a href="#L124">124</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  That's what I call it. As a matter of fact, Captain, I didn't crash here. I was brought here in my disabled ship. I was almost dead. The Companion saved my life.</td></tr>

<tr id="L125"><td><a href="#L125">125</a></td><td>SPOCK:  You were injured?</td></tr>

<tr id="L126"><td><a href="#L126">126</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  I was dying, Mister Spock.</td></tr>

<tr id="L127"><td><a href="#L127">127</a></td><td>KIRK:  You seem perfectly all right now. What was the matter?</td></tr>

<tr id="L128"><td><a href="#L128">128</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  I was an old man.</td></tr>

<tr id="L129"><td><a href="#L129">129</a></td><td>KIRK:  You were what?</td></tr>

<tr id="L130"><td><a href="#L130">130</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  Well, I don't know how it did it, but the Companion rejuvenated me, made me young again, like I am now.</td></tr>

<tr id="L131"><td><a href="#L131">131</a></td><td>SPOCK:  I prefer to reserve judgment on that part of your story, sir. Meanwhile, would you please explain exactly what this Companion of yours is?</td></tr>

<tr id="L132"><td><a href="#L132">132</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  I told you, I don't know what it is. It exists, it lives, and I can communicate with it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L133"><td><a href="#L133">133</a></td><td>MCCOY:  That's a pretty far out story.</td></tr>

<tr id="L134"><td><a href="#L134">134</a></td><td>KIRK:  Mister Cochrane, do you have a first name?</td></tr>

<tr id="L135"><td><a href="#L135">135</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  Zefram.</td></tr>

<tr id="L136"><td><a href="#L136">136</a></td><td>KIRK:  Zefram Cochrane of Alpha Centuri, the discoverer of the space warp?</td></tr>

<tr id="L137"><td><a href="#L137">137</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  That's right, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L138"><td><a href="#L138">138</a></td><td>MCCOY:  But that's impossible. Zefram Cochrane died a hundred and fifty years ago.</td></tr>

<tr id="L139"><td><a href="#L139">139</a></td><td>SPOCK:  The name of Zefram Cochrane is revered throughout the known galaxy. Planets were named after him. Great universities, cities.</td></tr>

<tr id="L140"><td><a href="#L140">140</a></td><td>KIRK:  Isn't your story a little improbable, Mister Cochrane?</td></tr>

<tr id="L141"><td><a href="#L141">141</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  No, it's true. I was eighty seven years old when I came here.</td></tr>

<tr id="L142"><td><a href="#L142">142</a></td><td>KIRK:  You say this Companion found you and rejuvenated you? What were you doing in space at the age of eighty seven?</td></tr>

<tr id="L143"><td><a href="#L143">143</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  I was tired, Captain. I was going to die, and I wanted to die in space. That's all.</td></tr>

<tr id="L144"><td><a href="#L144">144</a></td><td>SPOCK:  True, his body was never found.</td></tr>

<tr id="L145"><td><a href="#L145">145</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  You're looking at it, Mister Spock.</td></tr>

<tr id="L146"><td><a href="#L146">146</a></td><td>SPOCK:  If so, you wear your age very well.</td></tr>

<tr id="L147"><td><a href="#L147">147</a></td><td>MCCOY:  How do you feel?</td></tr>

<tr id="L148"><td><a href="#L148">148</a></td><td>NANCY:  Terrible. How should I feel?</td></tr>

<tr id="L149"><td><a href="#L149">149</a></td><td>MCCOY:  You're running a little temperature. Perhaps you should lie down.</td></tr>

<tr id="L150"><td><a href="#L150">150</a></td><td>NANCY:  Doctor, will you please just leave me alone. It's the heat.</td></tr>

<tr id="L151"><td><a href="#L151">151</a></td><td>MCCOY:  All right. Try to relax. Jim, it's started, the fever. It's over a hundred, and it's climbing.</td></tr>

<tr id="L152"><td><a href="#L152">152</a></td><td>KIRK:  How long do we have?</td></tr>

<tr id="L153"><td><a href="#L153">153</a></td><td>MCCOY:  A matter of hours, that's all.</td></tr>

<tr id="L154"><td><a href="#L154">154</a></td><td>KIRK:  Mister Cochrane, you say you were brought here a hundred and fifty years ago? You don't look over thirty five.</td></tr>

<tr id="L155"><td><a href="#L155">155</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  I haven't aged. The Companion sees to that.</td></tr>

<tr id="L156"><td><a href="#L156">156</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Captain. These instruments, they date from the time indicated. From your ship, Mister Cochrane?</td></tr>

<tr id="L157"><td><a href="#L157">157</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  I cannibalised it. The food, water, gardens, everything else I need the Companion gives me. Apparently, it creates it out of the native elements.</td></tr>

<tr id="L158"><td><a href="#L158">158</a></td><td>KIRK:  You say you can communicate with it. Perhaps you can find out what we're doing here.</td></tr>

<tr id="L159"><td><a href="#L159">159</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  I already know.</td></tr>

<tr id="L160"><td><a href="#L160">160</a></td><td>KIRK:  You wouldn't mind telling us?</td></tr>

<tr id="L161"><td><a href="#L161">161</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  You won't like it.</td></tr>

