<tr id="L312"><td><a href="#L312">312</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  Is this what the future holds? Men who have no notion of decency or morality? Maybe I'm a hundred and fifty years out of style, but I'm not going to be fodder for any inhuman monster. (leaves)</td></tr>

<tr id="L313"><td><a href="#L313">313</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Fascinating. A totally parochial attitude.</td></tr>

<tr id="L314"><td><a href="#L314">314</a></td><td>NANCY:  Doctor. Doctor.</td></tr>

<tr id="L315"><td><a href="#L315">315</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Right here, Miss Hedford.</td></tr>

<tr id="L316"><td><a href="#L316">316</a></td><td>NANCY:  I heard him. He was loved and he resents it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L317"><td><a href="#L317">317</a></td><td>MCCOY:  You just rest.</td></tr>

<tr id="L318"><td><a href="#L318">318</a></td><td>NANCY:  No. I don't want to die. I've been good at my job, but I've never been loved. Never. What kind of life is that? Not to be loved, never to have shown love? And he runs away from love. (cries)</td></tr>

<tr id="L319"><td><a href="#L319">319</a></td><td>SOMEONE: Ship's log, stardate 3220.3. Lieutenant Commander Scott reporting in lieu of the Captain and the first officer. We are continuing our search for the missing shuttlecraft.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Bridge</td></tr>
<tr id="L320"><td><a href="#L320">320</a></td><td>SULU:  Approaching what seems to be an asteroid belt, sir. Scanners report approximately seven thousand bodies of sizes running from types A to N.</td></tr>

<tr id="L321"><td><a href="#L321">321</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Atmosphere count?</td></tr>

<tr id="L322"><td><a href="#L322">322</a></td><td>SULU:  Approximately thirty four percent of the bodies of atmospherian types H to M.</td></tr>

<tr id="L323"><td><a href="#L323">323</a></td><td>SCOTT:  All right, then. We'll do it the hard way. All sensors set for life form registration. Automatic selection.</td></tr>

<tr id="L324"><td><a href="#L324">324</a></td><td>UHURA:  Mister Scott, there are thousands of them out there they could be on, if they're on any of them at all.</td></tr>

<tr id="L325"><td><a href="#L325">325</a></td><td>SCOTT:  That's right, Lieutenant. Thousands. And we'll look them over one by one.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Outside Cochrane's home</td></tr>
<tr id="L326"><td><a href="#L326">326</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Another contact session is in progress.</td></tr>

<tr id="L327"><td><a href="#L327">327</a></td><td>KIRK:  Companion, do you love the man?</td></tr>

<tr id="L328"><td><a href="#L328">328</a></td><td>COMPANION:  I do not understand.</td></tr>

<tr id="L329"><td><a href="#L329">329</a></td><td>KIRK:  Is he important to you, more important than anything? Is he as though he were a part of you?</td></tr>

<tr id="L330"><td><a href="#L330">330</a></td><td>COMPANION:  He is part of me. The man must continue.</td></tr>

<tr id="L331"><td><a href="#L331">331</a></td><td>KIRK:  He will not continue. He will cease to exist. By your feeling for him, you are condemning him to an existence he will find unbearable. He will cease to exist.</td></tr>

<tr id="L332"><td><a href="#L332">332</a></td><td>COMPANION:  He does not age. He remains forever.</td></tr>

<tr id="L333"><td><a href="#L333">333</a></td><td>KIRK:  You speak of his body. I speak of his spirit. Companion, inside the shelter, a female of our species is dying. She will not continue. That is what will happen to the man unless you release all of us.</td></tr>

<tr id="L334"><td><a href="#L334">334</a></td><td>COMPANION:  I do not understand.</td></tr>

<tr id="L335"><td><a href="#L335">335</a></td><td>KIRK:  Our species can only survive if we have obstacles to overcome. You take away all obstacles. Without them to strengthen us, we will weaken and die. You regard the man only as a toy. You amuse yourself with him.</td></tr>

<tr id="L336"><td><a href="#L336">336</a></td><td>COMPANION:  You are wrong. The man is the centre of all things. I care for him.</td></tr>

<tr id="L337"><td><a href="#L337">337</a></td><td>KIRK:  But you can't really love him. You haven't the slightest knowledge of love, the total union of two people. You are the Companion. He is the man. You are two different things. You can't join. You can't love. You may keep him here forever, but you will always be separate, apart from him.</td></tr>

<tr id="L338"><td><a href="#L338">338</a></td><td>COMPANION:  If I were human there can be love? (vanishes)</td></tr>

<tr id="L339"><td><a href="#L339">339</a></td><td>MCCOY:  What did you hope to gain by that, Jim?</td></tr>

<tr id="L340"><td><a href="#L340">340</a></td><td>KIRK:  Try to convince her of the hopelessness of it. Love sometimes expresses itself in sacrifice. I thought maybe if she loved him, she'd let him go.</td></tr>

<tr id="L341"><td><a href="#L341">341</a></td><td>SPOCK:  But she or it is inhuman, Captain. You cannot expect her to react like a human.</td></tr>

<tr id="L342"><td><a href="#L342">342</a></td><td>KIRK:  I tried.</td></tr>

<tr id="L343"><td><a href="#L343">343</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  It's useless. I know.</td></tr>

<tr id="L344"><td><a href="#L344">344</a></td><td>NANCY:  (standing in the doorway) Zefram Cochrane.</td></tr>

<tr id="L345"><td><a href="#L345">345</a></td><td>KIRK:  Bones?</td></tr>

<tr id="L346"><td><a href="#L346">346</a></td><td>MCCOY:  I don't understand it. She's not sick at all.</td></tr>

<tr id="L347"><td><a href="#L347">347</a></td><td>NANCY:  We understand.</td></tr>

<tr id="L348"><td><a href="#L348">348</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  It's her.</td></tr>

<tr id="L349"><td><a href="#L349">349</a></td><td>KIRK:  What?</td></tr>

<tr id="L350"><td><a href="#L350">350</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  Don't you understand? It's the Companion.</td></tr>

<tr id="L351"><td><a href="#L351">351</a></td><td>KIRK:  Bones?</td></tr>

<tr id="L352"><td><a href="#L352">352</a></td><td>MCCOY:  She's perfectly healthy. Heart like a hammer, respiration normal, blood pressure normal. This is medically impossible.</td></tr>

<tr id="L353"><td><a href="#L353">353</a></td><td>NANCY:  We are here.</td></tr>

<tr id="L354"><td><a href="#L354">354</a></td><td>KIRK:  We?</td></tr>

<tr id="L355"><td><a href="#L355">355</a></td><td>NANCY:  Both of us. Those you knew as the Commissioner and the Companion. We are both here.</td></tr>

<tr id="L356"><td><a href="#L356">356</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Companion, you do not have the power to create life.</td></tr>

<tr id="L357"><td><a href="#L357">357</a></td><td>NANCY:  That is for the Maker of all things.</td></tr>

<tr id="L358"><td><a href="#L358">358</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Commissioner Hedford was dying.</td></tr>

<tr id="L359"><td><a href="#L359">359</a></td><td>NANCY:  That part of us was too weak to hold on. In a moment, there would have been no continuing. Now we're together.</td></tr>

<tr id="L360"><td><a href="#L360">360</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Then you are both here, in the one body?</td></tr>

<tr id="L361"><td><a href="#L361">361</a></td><td>NANCY:  We are one.</td></tr>

<tr id="L362"><td><a href="#L362">362</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: She goes to Cochrane, who takes a step back.</td></tr>

<tr id="L363"><td><a href="#L363">363</a></td><td>NANCY:  Zefram, we frighten you. We've never frightened you before. Loneliness. This is loneliness. Oh, what a bitter thing. Oh, Zefram, it's so sad. How do you bear it, this loneliness?</td></tr>

<tr id="L364"><td><a href="#L364">364</a></td><td>KIRK:  Spock, check out the shuttlecraft. Engine, communications, everything.</td></tr>

<tr id="L365"><td><a href="#L365">365</a></td><td>NANCY:  That will not be necessary, Captain. Your vehicle will operate as before, so will the communications device.</td></tr>

<tr id="L366"><td><a href="#L366">366</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  You're letting us go?</td></tr>

<tr id="L367"><td><a href="#L367">367</a></td><td>NANCY:  We could do nothing now to stop you. You said we would not know love because we were not human. Now we are human. We'll know the change of days. We will know death. But to touch the hand of man, nothing is as important.</td></tr>

<tr id="L368"><td><a href="#L368">368</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  You're very beautiful.</td></tr>

<tr id="L369"><td><a href="#L369">369</a></td><td>NANCY:  Part of me understands. Part does not. But it pleases me.</td></tr>

<tr id="L370"><td><a href="#L370">370</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  I could explain many things.</td></tr>

<tr id="L371"><td><a href="#L371">371</a></td><td>NANCY:  Oh, let me walk, Zefram. Let me feel the earth against my feet. Let me feel the warmth of the sun on my face. You beside me. Let me feel these things.</td></tr>

<tr id="L372"><td><a href="#L372">372</a></td><td>KIRK:  Go ahead, Cochrane We have a few things to do.</td></tr>

<tr id="L373"><td><a href="#L373">373</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Cochrane and Nancy walk off hand in hand.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Bridge</td></tr>
<tr id="L374"><td><a href="#L374">374</a></td><td>UHURA:  Mister Scott, it's the Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L375"><td><a href="#L375">375</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Put him on. Lock on to his co-ordinates. Captain, this is Scotty. Are you all right?</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Outside Cochrane's home</td></tr>
<tr id="L376"><td><a href="#L376">376</a></td><td>KIRK:  Perfectly all right. Can you get a fix on us.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Bridge</td></tr>
<tr id="L377"><td><a href="#L377">377</a></td><td>SCOTT:  The helm is computing your position now, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L378"><td><a href="#L378">378</a></td><td>SULU:  Course two twenty four mark twelve. ETA fifty seven minutes.</td></tr>

<tr id="L379"><td><a href="#L379">379</a></td><td>SCOTT:  We'll be there in 57 minutes, sir.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Outside Cochrane's home</td></tr>
<tr id="L380"><td><a href="#L380">380</a></td><td>KIRK:  Very good. I'll continue transmitting. Assume standard orbit when you arrive. We'll transport up in the shuttlecraft.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Bridge</td></tr>
<tr id="L381"><td><a href="#L381">381</a></td><td>SCOTT:  What happened, Captain?</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Outside Cochrane's home</td></tr>
<tr id="L382"><td><a href="#L382">382</a></td><td>KIRK:  Interesting story, Scotty. I can't tell you now because, quite frankly, I don't know how it's going to end. Kirk out.</td></tr>

<tr id="L383"><td><a href="#L383">383</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Somewhere in the vicinity, Nancy is holding up her scarf to mimic how she saw Cochrane when she was a swirly thing.</td></tr>

<tr id="L384"><td><a href="#L384">384</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  Everything will be an eye-opener to you. There's a thousand planets out there, a thousand races, and I'll show everything to you, soon as I learn my way around again. Maybe I can make up a little for everything you've done for me.</td></tr>

<tr id="L385"><td><a href="#L385">385</a></td><td>NANCY:  I can't go with you, Zefram.</td></tr>

<tr id="L386"><td><a href="#L386">386</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  Of course you can. You have to.</td></tr>

<tr id="L387"><td><a href="#L387">387</a></td><td>NANCY:  My life emanates from this place. If I should leave it for more than a tiny march of days, I'll cease to exist. I must return, even as you must consume matter to maintain your life.</td></tr>

<tr id="L388"><td><a href="#L388">388</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  You gave up everything to be human? But even if you stay here, you'll eventually die.</td></tr>

<tr id="L389"><td><a href="#L389">389</a></td><td>NANCY:  The joy of this hour. I am pleased.</td></tr>

<tr id="L390"><td><a href="#L390">390</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  Well, I can't just fly away and leave you here.</td></tr>

<tr id="L391"><td><a href="#L391">391</a></td><td>NANCY:  You must be free, Zefram Cochrane.</td></tr>

<tr id="L392"><td><a href="#L392">392</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  You saved my life, took care of me. You loved me. I never understood. I do now.</td></tr>

<tr id="L393"><td><a href="#L393">393</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: He kisses her.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Bridge</td></tr>
<tr id="L394"><td><a href="#L394">394</a></td><td>SCOTT:  We're locked in, Captain. Standard orbit established. Shuttlecraft bay standing by to receive you.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Outside Cochrane's home</td></tr>
<tr id="L395"><td><a href="#L395">395</a></td><td>KIRK:  Stand by, Scotty.</td></tr>

<tr id="L396"><td><a href="#L396">396</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Cochrane and Nancy return.</td></tr>

<tr id="L397"><td><a href="#L397">397</a></td><td>KIRK:  The Enterprise is waiting, Mister Cochrane.</td></tr>

<tr id="L398"><td><a href="#L398">398</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  I can't take her away from here. If I do, she'll die. If I leave her, she'll die of loneliness. I owe everything to her. I can't leave her. I love her. Is that surprising?</td></tr>

<tr id="L399"><td><a href="#L399">399</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Not coming from a human being. You are, after all, essentially irrational.</td></tr>

<tr id="L400"><td><a href="#L400">400</a></td><td>KIRK:  Think it over, Mister Cochrane. There's a whole galaxy out there waiting to honour you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L401"><td><a href="#L401">401</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  I have honours enough.</td></tr>

<tr id="L402"><td><a href="#L402">402</a></td><td>SPOCK:  But you will age, both of you. There will be no immortality. You'll both grow old here and finally die.</td></tr>

<tr id="L403"><td><a href="#L403">403</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  That's been happening to men and women for a long time. I've got the feeling it's one of the pleasanter things about being human, as long as you grow old together.</td></tr>

<tr id="L404"><td><a href="#L404">404</a></td><td>KIRK:  Are you sure?</td></tr>

<tr id="L405"><td><a href="#L405">405</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  There's plenty of water here. The climate's good for growing things. I might try to plant a fig tree. A man's entitled to that, isn't he? It isn't gratitude, Captain. Now that I see her, touch her, I know that I love her. We'll have a lot of years together. They'll be happy ones.</td></tr>

<tr id="L406"><td><a href="#L406">406</a></td><td>KIRK:  All the best.</td></tr>

<tr id="L407"><td><a href="#L407">407</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: They shake hands, and Kirk walks away.</td></tr>

<tr id="L408"><td><a href="#L408">408</a></td><td>COCHRANE:  Captain, don't tell them about me.</td></tr>

<tr id="L409"><td><a href="#L409">409</a></td><td>KIRK:  Not a word, Mister Cochrane.</td></tr>

<tr id="L410"><td><a href="#L410">410</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Jim, what about that war on Epsilon Canaris Three?</td></tr>

<tr id="L411"><td><a href="#L411">411</a></td><td>KIRK:  Well, I'm sure the Federation can find another woman somewhere who'll stop that war.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>END CREDITS</td></tr>
